titles: Die Veneris, 31 Augusti, 1649. Resolved (upon the question) by the Commons assembled in Parliament, that Mr. Walter Mountagu do within ten days next ensuing, depart this nation, and all the dominions thereof ... Resolved, &c. That Sir Kenelm Digby do depart this nation ... Resolved, &c. That the estate and estates of all such person or persons as shall or do conceal Sir John Winter, Mr. Walter Mountagu, and Sir Kenelm Digby, or any of them, shall be sequestred ...
author: England and Wales. Parliament. House of Commons.
publisher: Printed by John Field, printer to the Parliament of England.,
notes: Reproduction of original in the Henry E. Huntington Library.
